/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Noslom<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukayneironguard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kayne Ironguard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 8:13:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14750.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: physical enhancement, and mind and body rejuvenation</span><hr size=1> I saved up 5 points and put it into Physical enhancement.<br><br>After training the 5 points into it, I recieved nothing.  Not a single hitpoint.  Wether it also really adds extra mitigation / avoidance is not noticeable at all, I certainly don't seem to be getting hit for any less or being missed more. <br><br>Maybe this skill doesn't kick in until you get the 3 linked skills maxed?  If so then I'd have appreciated some sort of notice as Physical enhancement doesn't specify what previous skills you must have maxed to gain the benefit of Physical Enhancement, other than spending X amounts of AA points on the previous page of abilitys.<br><br>As it is I've just burnt 5 points and I'm left feeling a tad cheated.  I petitioned not long after training the points...camped and came back a couple times just to make sure my char was updated.  the GM said that maybe it is a bug and reported it.  I don't think a refund is very likely so looking like I've just got to suck this waste of 5 points until I max out Natural Durability / mitigation and avoidance.<br><br>Wish I had of just kept them and trained CF lvl 2 or even saved one more point for 2h bash.  They would certainly be moer beneficial to me right now that what I've ended up with.<br><br>Ah well, live and learn.<br><br>Kayne <p></p><i></i>